==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inculpate
<hw>In*cul"pate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Inculpated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Inculpating</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[LL.
<ets>inculpatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>inculpare</ets> to blame; pref.
<ets>in-</ets> in + <ets>culpa</ets> fault. See
<er>Culpable</er>.]</ety> <note>[A word of recent introduction.]</note>
<def>To blame; to impute guilt to; to accuse; to involve or implicate in
guilt. Contrasted with <contr>exculpate</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That risk could only exculpate her and not <qex>inculpate</qex>
them -- the probabilities protected them so perfectly.</q> <rj><qau>H.
James.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inculpation</ent>⟦br⟧
